{"bill":{"bill_id":1650029,"change_hash":"e4219453720f4ce2e6b4e092104f8bbe","session_id":2021,"session":{"session_id":2021,"state_id":14,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IN\/bill\/HB1177\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/iga.in.gov\/legislative\/2023\/bills\/house\/1177\/","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-15","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-10","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-09","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-15","event":2}],"state":"IN","state_id":14,"bill_number":"HB1177","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":37,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":37,"title":"Handgun training for teachers.","description":"Handgun training for teachers. Creates a specialized firearms safety, education, and training curriculum (curriculum) for teachers, school staff, and school employees. Specifies curriculum requirements. Authorizes funds from the: (1) Indiana safe schools fund; (2) Indiana secured schools fund; and (3) school corporation and charter school safety advance program; to be used for the purpose of providing specialized firearms instruction to certain teachers, school staff, and school employees, and for providing counseling services to students, teachers, school staff, and school employees in the event of a school shooting. Requires a charter school, nonpublic school, or school corporation to ensure that a teacher, school staff member, or school employee who receives a grant from the Indiana safe schools fund for the purpose of receiving specialized firearms instruction complies with certain requirements. Provides that the identity of any person who: (1) enrolls in; (2) participates in; or (3) completes; the curriculum is confidential. Provides that a public school or an accredited nonpublic school may not conduct a training or drill for an employee of the school that includes, as any part of the training or drill, the expelling of any type of projectile at the employee unless: (1) the school informs the employee of the use of projectiles in the training or drill; and (2) the employee consents, in writing, to the use of projectiles during the training or drill. Provides that a public school or an accredited nonpublic school may not conduct or approve a training or drill for a student of the school that includes, as any part of the training or drill, the expelling of any type of projectile. Authorizes a qualified retired law enforcement officer to carry or possess a firearm on school property. Makes conforming and technical amendments.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-10","committee_id":1288,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"name":"Education"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Authored by Representative Lucas","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"First reading: referred to Committee on Education","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Representative Lehman added as coauthor","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-19","action":"Representative Judy added as coauthor","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-07","action":"Representative Teshka J added as coauthor","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-09","action":"Committee report: do pass, adopted","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-13","action":"Amendment #1 (DeLaney) failed; Roll Call 100: yeas 29, nays 67","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-13","action":"Amendment #2 (DeLaney) failed; Roll Call 101: yeas 30, nays 66","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-13","action":"Second reading: ordered engrossed","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-14","a